<item>
            <title>[SPR-3002] forms:errors doesn&apos;t make use of nestedPath</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-3002</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The form:errors doesn&apos;t take nestedPath into account.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was annoying for me since I was making use of nestedPath on a few objects that had identical fields. This resulted in non-validating xhtml.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In ErrorsTag.java, I replaced:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;protected String autogenerateId() throws JspException {&lt;br/&gt;
	return getPath() + &quot;.errors&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;protected String autogenerateId() throws JspException {&lt;br/&gt;
	String path = getNestedPath() == null&lt;br/&gt;
		? getPath() : getNestedPath() + getPath();&lt;br/&gt;
	return path + &quot;.errors&quot;;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This seemed to produce a more sane result, however, I&apos;m not familiar enough to know if this is correct.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
